<subSubSection id="C5708DAF3445A5F49AF2EA97F1262DC4" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="type locality">
<paragraph id="F8206FF6E1BBD0C144FA699A65824F15" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3F292514DE0D6AFB8291D38AC4BE9219" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Very shallow, slowly flowing, meandering stream (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9AA59DE384E7DF4078A9672D58254618" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Stream in primary forest of Gunung Mulu National Park, Sarawak, type locality of Okalia necopinata sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.79635.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668223" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">6</figureCitation>
), which is entirely shaded by the trees of a primary dipterocarp forest in the limestone area of Gunung Mulu National Park, ca 
<geoCoordinate id="FD0A58A1722B18D9CABCB0DE10A79694" degrees="4" direction="north" minutes="02" orientation="latitude" precision="1" seconds="59.5" value="4.049861">4°02'59.5&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="E983F0C0F463286886D0547C29A2A770" degrees="114" direction="east" minutes="49" orientation="longitude" precision="1" seconds="24.3" value="114.82342">114°49'24.3&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 70 m a.s.l. (north-eastern Sarawak, Borneo, Malaysia). The stream is ca 1 m wide, with a few deeper pools, and contains large amounts of accumulated leaves; the bottom is sandy with fine gravel and wood debris; the muddy banks are densely covered with 
<taxonomicName id="0A83D9D41D88A74C3E49481B70C7DB82" authorityName="M.Hotta" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Araceae" genus="Phymatarum" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phymatarum borneense" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borneense">
<emphasis id="68A8F6D5BD2F53D002D8367F01932AF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Phymatarum borneense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. [Note. Unfortunately, 
<bibRefCitation id="423379D88D5FCB86AC5E99AB945206AF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.912.47796" author="Kodada, J" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="25 - 64" refId="B10" refString="Kodada, J, Jaech, MA, Freitag, H, Ciamporova-Zatovicova, Z, Goffova, K, Selnekovic, D, Ciampor, F, 2020a. Ancyronyx clisteri, a new spider riffle beetle species from Borneo, redescription of A. sarawacensis Jaech including a description of the larva and new distribution data for A. procerus Jaech using DNA barcodes (Coleoptera, Elmidae). ZooKeys 912: 25 - 64, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.912.47796" title="Ancyronyx clisteri, a new spider riffle beetle species from Borneo, redescription of A. sarawacensis Jaech including a description of the larva and new distribution data for A. procerus Jaech using DNA barcodes (Coleoptera, Elmidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.912.47796" volume="912" year="2020 a">Kodada et al. (2020a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="17723D7FB4CF6ED24DE3BDA394DEAE76" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1003.55541" author="Kodada, J" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="31 - 55" refId="B11" refString="Kodada, J, Jaech, MA, Freitag, H, Ciamporova-Zatovicova, Z, Goffova, K, Selnekovic, D, Ciampor, F, 2020b. Ancyronyx lianlabangorum sp. nov., a new spider riffle beetle from Sarawak, and new distribution records for A. pulcherrimus Kodada, Jaech &amp; Ciampor based on DNA barcodes (Coleoptera, Elmidae). ZooKeys 1003: 31 - 55, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1003.55541" title="Ancyronyx lianlabangorum sp. nov., a new spider riffle beetle from Sarawak, and new distribution records for A. pulcherrimus Kodada, Jaech &amp; Ciampor based on DNA barcodes (Coleoptera, Elmidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1003.55541" volume="1003" year="2020 b">2020b</bibRefCitation>
) provided incorrect coordinates for this locality for 
<taxonomicName id="FE408F9E1E9E847F38E9C5451E04C58A" authorityName="Kodada, Jach &amp; Ciampor" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Ancyronyx" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ancyronyx pulcherrimus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulcherrimus">
<emphasis id="C28AFEA672B442B78B8057813DA3A578" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ancyronyx pulcherrimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kodada, 
<normalizedToken id="C7DB6E352E1F23370613BFAA524F33C0" originalValue="Jäch">Jaech</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="7E4C2CD34F9FB6FD5981A2AAEE4A5094" originalValue="Čiampor">Ciampor</normalizedToken>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7120BCC0DE086D4692013D42CA4DAD1A" class="Insecta" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. sarawacensis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarawacensis">
<emphasis id="4B1534442DA264847C7DB882DC9596A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">A. sarawacensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="FA64824E24765F4630AC4D5B90E643B7" originalValue="Jäch">Jaech</normalizedToken>
].
</paragraph>
<caption id="20E1A3CD9B091E2174109235B967DBAB" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.79635.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668223" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
